  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A geriatric assessment is becoming increasingly important in the treatment of patients with a
      percutaneous aortic valve replacement due to their comorbidities. The aim of this multimodal
      therapy concept is to examine the influence on the postoperative outcome. In addition to a
      comprehensive assessment of the individual frailty score, the subjective condition before and
      after TAVI is also evaluated using a standardized questionnaire (&quot;Minnesota living with heart
      failure questionnaire&quot;).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
